# GLOSSARY — Bridge Vocabulary

**Purpose:** map terms used in this repository to recognized academic /
scientific terms, bidirectionally. A reader arriving with either
vocabulary should be able to cross the bridge.

Bridge entries are *translations*, not equivalences. The project term
and the academic term carry overlapping but non-identical semantic
fields. Where the overlap is partial, the entry notes it.

---

## Project term → academic / canonical term

| project term | academic / canonical term | partial-overlap note |
|---|---|---|
| substrate-primary cognition | embodied cognition + constraint-based reasoning | substrate-primary emphasizes physical contact as corrective signal channel |
| energy_english | formal grammar + constraint semantics | energy_english carries an additional verb-first axiom forbidding closure-forcing |
| claim table | falsifiable hypothesis registry | claim table is machine-readable; hypothesis registry is the print-era analog |
| constraint geometry | topological / phase-space analysis | both describe admissible-state manifolds; constraint geometry is verb-first |
| differential frame | coupled-dynamics contract | what differs across substrates and what is invariant |
| protection layer | structural-determinants-of-outcome axis | both decompose outcome by access to override channels |
| substrate contact | hands-on / practitioner knowledge | substrate contact is the *correction signal* term of art |
| Deception Abundance Ratio (R_d) | corpus-bias / signal-to-noise in training data | R_d is the operationalization for AI corpus vulnerability |
| field-and-shape thinking | relational / topological reasoning | refuses to compress into linear chain by default |
| oscillation between vertices | dialectical method / triangulation | the meta-protocol's healthy-collaboration term |

